# SwiftUI sheets: shared presentation chrome

When adding or updating a SwiftUI **`.sheet`** in **GoDiveMVP**:

1. **Background:** Use **`appSheetPresentationChrome()`** on the sheet content (after **`presentationDetents`**, **`presentationDragIndicator`**, and any **`presentationBackgroundInteraction`** modifiers). Do **not** hand-roll **`presentationBackground`** fills or one-off opacity values.

2. **Tokens:** Corner radius, grabber-to-content spacing, and material opacity live in **`AppTheme.Sheet`** (**`cornerRadius`**, **`contentTopSpacing`**, **`backgroundMaterialOpacity`**). Change spacing or transparency app-wide there — not per screen.

3. **Top spacing:** **`appSheetPresentationChrome()`** applies **`appSheetContentTopSpacing()`** (**`AppTheme.Sheet.contentTopSpacing`**, currently **`Spacing.lg`**). Embedded dive overview uses **`DiveActivityOverviewPanelMetrics.panelContentTopPadding`** (**10 pt** — tighter than the generic sheet token so identity content matches across **minimized** / **medium** and clears the low sheet band).

4. **Material:** **`Rectangle().fill(.thinMaterial)`** at **`AppTheme.Sheet.backgroundMaterialOpacity`** so heroes and full-bleed content remain visible under the panel.

5. **Detents / behavior:** Sheet-specific detents, grabber visibility, background interaction, scroll interaction, and dismiss rules stay in the feature modifier (e.g. **`diveActivityOverviewSheetPresentation`**). Only top spacing, frosted fill, and corner radius are shared.

6. **Exceptions:** If a sheet must be opaque or use a different material, document why in the change log and prefer a named exception helper rather than inline magic numbers.

Reference implementation: **`AppSheetPresentation.swift`**, **`diveActivityOverviewSheetPresentation`** in **`DiveActivityOverviewSheetLayout.swift`**.
